Just try to create a subtask that has a large image as a custom icon for the issuetype. The image in the screenshot is a pink concrete jungle wet dream tomato meme

User asked for feature request in here : [GHS-4198|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/GHS-4198]

Quoting his comment : 
{quote}
In our Scrum project the ScrumMaster needs to ensure that every Team Member changed the 'Remaining Estimate' of his tasks every day.
Therefore we need the possibility to get a view that shows all issues that are 'In Progress' but has no CHANGED 'Remaining Estimate' at this day. With that result the ScrumMaster is able to tell the assignee that he should change the 'Remaining Estimate' for his tasks. This will keep focuessed and help us to have a hour burndown that is 'latest' as possible.
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-4822].
  {panel}

We would like to see the ability to customize the rapid board and especially change the color of cards (sticky's) based on project.

Until we get an update like this the rapid board is not a suitable enterprise option.

a user report in ticket in our support channel : [GHS-4190|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/GHS-4190] 
{quote}
For big product backlogs, re-prioritising a task from the bottom of the backlog to the top requires dragging it up the table to the desired loaction. If multiple tasks need to be moved it takes a long time, particularly if the refresh speed on the browser is slow (as it might be over a remote connection).

It would be great to have an option to tag one or more issues in the backlog, then navigate to the desired insertion point and select an option to move/insert those tagged issues at that point.
{quote}

